Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.39,0:00:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand, a shooting comet,\Na wind-up doll, and a crowd!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.60,0:00:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mystery-solving logic drenches\Ndry hearts and sand walls!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.15,0:00:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is about\Ngreed and 1 billion yen in gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.41,0:00:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.29,0:00:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.17,0:00:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.63,0:01:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Ryujin-Maru\N{\i0}disappeared seven years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with 1 billion yen in gold onboard,\Nbut suddenly reappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.93,0:02:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the gold was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man was invited to the island,\Nwhich had garnered attention
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the ghost ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.02,0:02:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came here as tourists,\Nbut the mayor's true motive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.24,0:02:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to have the old man\Nlocate the missing gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.49,0:02:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone tried to kill\Nhim at his lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.08,0:02:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was Hamada,\Nthe lighthouse keeper with facial burns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the suspicious travel agent\NUehara seemed to know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who exactly are these two?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, the old man\Nwas attacked by a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After narrowly escaping death,\Nhe chased his assailant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.43,0:02:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone knocked him\Nunconscious and framed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.35,0:02:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...as Hamada's killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.78,0:03:04.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ghost Ship Murder Case (Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ghost Ship Murder Case (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you're a famous detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:10.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeo Mikami (50)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can't get away with murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.00,0:03:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it all wrong! This guy\Nsuddenly attacked me in my sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I chased him here,\Ngot hit from behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when I woke up he was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably just\Nkilled him in a rage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.55,0:03:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this outfit\Nhe's wearing is kept in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Suigun Artifact Museum...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.89,0:03:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why another Suigun outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.15,0:03:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be the curse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it has to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.32,0:03:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Hamada got possessed\Nand dressed up like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet! The curse is\Njust a superstition!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.66,0:03:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why's he dressed like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.24,0:03:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. There's no\Npoint in arguing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sword wound is what killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did his sleeve come\Noff during the struggle?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are rope marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Covered in cuts. But these ones are--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.23,0:04:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Children shouldn't\Nlook at such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Where are you going,\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! You'll get in\Ntrouble for barging in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it.\NHamada-{\i1}san {\i0}was killed here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that blood?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Get that officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does look like\Nhe was murdered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.97,0:04:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't clear\Nthe detective's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghosts got mad because\Nan outsider was poking around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna protect him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.61,0:05:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be cursed too, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look good...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What's here? The Suigun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.34,0:05:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.63,0:05:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who did it,\Nbut if they think they can frame me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with such a childish trick,\Nthey're greatly mistaken!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you didn't do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was dead long before I got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.98,0:05:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give us that crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pool of blood on\Nthe boat is proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I killed him, then he\Nonly died thirty minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the blood on the boat\Nis completely dry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.62,0:05:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However you look at it,\Nthree to four hours have passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.45,0:05:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My attacker was someone\Nother than Hamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That person killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After killing him, they attacked\Nme in Suigun armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To lure me here and frame me\Nas Hamada's murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.81,0:06:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That person tied Hamada up\Nin the boat and tortured him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rope marks on\Nhis wrists are proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cuts all over his body are\Ntoo numerous and shallow to be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.32,0:06:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer\Ntied him up and tortured him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.91,0:06:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd do something so horrible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamada was probably\Nconnected to the {\i1}Ryujin-Maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.38,0:06:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.55,0:06:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Ryujin-Maru{\i0}'s telescope\Nwas on the lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:06:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:06:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing a great\Ndetective doesn't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.44,0:07:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Hamada appeared\Nseven years ago, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.98,0:07:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was the gold's location\Nthat the killer got from Hamada?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Hamada most likely\Nknew where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he moved\Nto the island to guard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he feared I would find it,\Nso he attempted to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan and Suzu-{\i1}kun {\i0}even saw\Nhim leave from the backstage door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzu did?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was yet another\Nperson looking for the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.35,0:07:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that person's eyes,\NHamada and I were both obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would explain the set up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no one here like that--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's him! That other person from Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:07:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The travel agent?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.62,0:07:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was fighting with Hamada!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The inn, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it! Believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we know you didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.64,0:08:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer! Get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.39,0:08:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've never arrested anyone before!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. What're you here for then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got cold feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deputy Mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to convince him\Nto turn himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.91,0:08:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the town hall\Nthat asked him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.03,0:08:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my responsibility\Nas Deputy Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been five minutes now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.31,0:09:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He ran off...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He escaped out the back! After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.53,0:09:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to persuade him,\Nbut he suddenly shot at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get you to a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be all right.\NIt's just a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of him around\Nthe back road. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.17,0:09:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of him here either. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work. Sorry, but could\Nyou leave some guards
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.76,0:09:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and come back for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! There's still this area!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't ask us to check\Nthe Suigun Cave...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.02,0:09:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody would dare go near that place.\NA single officer isn't really--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.86,0:10:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of cowardice is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.28,0:10:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get serious! Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.13,0:10:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Uehara killed Hamada-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nhe must've learned the gold's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if so, then why did he\Nneed to search the lighthouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:32.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No Entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moss?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the kind\Nthat grows on land!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.25,0:10:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right; this boat didn't sink!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But would it be possible to hide it\Nfrom the islanders for seven years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the Suigun Cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one would go near there! What if--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've noticed it had\Nhe looked through the telescope!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need\Nto torture Hamada-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:25.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Suigun Cave
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.95,0:11:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good. I'll get stopped if I'm seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.83,0:11:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you 'oh' me!\NYou wanna go to the cave, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I happen to know a secret path.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.51,0:11:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?! Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.05,0:11:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude! Can't you ask politely?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.97,0:11:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.73,0:11:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.60,0:11:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dummy! What're you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:11:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to, then fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.69,0:12:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! I'll show you the way!\NFollow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a bossy kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.08,0:12:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See! Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going in, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.34,0:12:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you didn't\Nbelieve in superstitions?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.26,0:12:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I don't! I only asked\Nbecause I'm concerned about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can stay here if you're scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.82,0:12:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a superstition, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:13:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Hamada-{\i1}san\N{\i0}used to look after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghosts are mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! You'll be punished!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those weren't ghosts just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a draft\Nresonating inside the cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.12,0:13:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These stairs aren't natural.\NSomeone purposely made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's bright up ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.31,0:14:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should make stairs\Nthat don't break, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This moss! This is the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.32,0:14:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no moss here.\NIt broke apart recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.96,0:14:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. The storm opened\Nup the exit and--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like something slid down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it.\NThe {\i1}Ryujin-Maru {\i0}was hidden here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The passageway that\Nthe {\i1}Ryujin-Maru {\i0}stayed in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was demolished by\Nthe storm and reopened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.84,0:15:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this was no suicide!\NIn which case, the killer is--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.36,0:15:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would really help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.41,0:15:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori! The fishermen\Nare going to lend us a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.66,0:15:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to go by the Suigun Cave!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Dad! Have you seen\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.00,0:15:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares?! He's probably\Noff playing somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.67,0:15:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably killed himself after\Naccepting that he couldn't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.10,0:16:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I followed you\Nwhen I saw you go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.06,0:16:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go back to town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was no suicide.\NHe was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at his wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hole on the right is bigger\Nthan the one on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This proves the bullet went\Nfrom left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet the gun is in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.71,0:16:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it unnatural to shoot from\Nthe left with your right hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.60,0:16:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, there's no longer\Nany need to hide the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun {\i0}doesn't seem surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.11,0:16:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shot yourself\Nin the arm, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even realized that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were burn marks\Non the hole in your shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that you fired\Nwith the muzzle pressed against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you\Nwere suddenly shot at.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.67,0:17:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody would 'suddenly'\Nshoot in such a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You impress me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You also killed Hamada-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I always\Nthought he seemed suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I checked the lighthouse\Nwhile he was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you found the telescope?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I planned to look for\Nthe gold someday at my leisure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the greedy mayor\Nstarted needlessly prying...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.03,0:17:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy's not greedy! He said\Nyou used the town's money!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I became nervous;\NKogoro Mori is a peerless detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.84,0:17:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried he might find the\Ngold first if he started investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he got involved, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you tricked the old man and\Nframed him as Hamada-{\i1}san{\i0}'s killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.02,0:18:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mistakenly underestimated him, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you did learn the gold's\Nlocation from Hamada-{\i1}san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.65,0:18:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally told me about\Nthis place after a bit of pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Mori said,\Nhe had been on the {\i1}Ryujin-Maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it this guy was, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Hamada threw him and the\Nowner into the stormy ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.75,0:18:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep all the gold for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.92,0:18:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamada. His real name\Nwas apparently Aoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He brought the {\i1}Ryujin-Maru\N{\i0}in here to escape the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the storm tore rocks off\Nand sealed the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.39,0:18:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably didn't plan to,\Nbut there were no other hiding places.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The islanders stayed away\Nbecause of the 'curse.'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.19,0:18:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more so after he killed\Nthe professor to make it look like
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Suigun curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.87,0:19:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he burned it himself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.95,0:19:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he feared someone\Nmight recognize him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pretended to get shot by\NUehara-{\i1}san {\i0}to let him escape, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.54,0:19:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he were arrested, Hamada-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nkiller and the gold's location
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.30,0:19:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. He did seem\Nvaguely aware of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you letting me run?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that; you're a\Ndead man if they catch you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold onto this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your situation will get even\Nworse if you're caught with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.42,0:19:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.05,0:20:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you beat him to\Nthe cave and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\NNow our discussion is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.93,0:20:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody'll find your bodies here! Ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.15,0:20:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.03,0:20:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably buried\Naround here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.32,0:20:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leisurely look for it\Nafter things cool down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd never find it in 100\Nyears with your intelligence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.70,0:20:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.12,0:20:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you know where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. At your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.39,0:20:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gold was in these blocks\Nused as part of the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:21:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! I love you, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.94,0:21:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.61,0:21:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An earthquake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this board to the exit!\NI'll bring Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.51,0:21:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.72,0:21:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.01,0:21:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.04,0:21:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's probably no way\Nto dig out the gold
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the completely-collapsed cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.13,0:22:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt anyone would\Nspend over a billion yen
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.96,0:22:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just to dig out a billion yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.80,0:22:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, the greed-inducing\Ngold returned to the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.81,0:22:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the Suigun curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.73,0:23:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! If I hadn't gone to\Nrescue you in the fishing boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.11,0:23:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no telling\Nwhat would've happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.49,0:23:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing to my\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.79,0:23:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.42,0:24:25.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.51,0:24:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.89,0:24:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it! Where did\Nthe killer disappear to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.23,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Could it be?!\NOnly he could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:31.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Giant Monster Gomera Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.11,0:24:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.36,0:24:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Giant Monster Gomera Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.92,0:24:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.37,0:24:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.47,0:24:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode Genta the \Nkaiju makes his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.21,0:24:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eel bowls!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.63,0:24:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
